Surely -- surely -- this Saturday is the one during which the Ohio State offense lives up to all of the expectations that were born and nurtured during the preseason. This just has to be the day when quarterback Cardale Jones pops the top on that bottle of magic from last season's postseason run to the national championship.
With a beleaguered Maryland team and its -- according to reports -- lame-duck coach coming into Ohio Stadium as the Buckeyes' homecoming opponent, what can go wrong?
Anything?
Whether you're at the game or watching on TV, a perfect complement to your game-day experience is following The Dispatch's Rob Oller for Scarlet and Gray Matter on Twitter .
For the past decade Oller has been entertaining Dispatch readers with his SGM columns on Sundays following OSU football games. Now you can receive SGM nuggets during the action. Rob can be found on Twitter at @rollerCD .
YOUR CHANCE AT FAME! (Sorry, fortune not guaranteed): Not only can you enjoy Scarlet & Gray Matter, you also have a chance to be a part of it. During his tweeting on Saturdays, Rob will pick the best readers' responses and include them in the next day's SGM . To wit, here's an excerpt from an edition of Scarlet & Gray Matter after Ohio State's victory over Michigan last season:

